Hi Tarun, I'm sorry to hear that you're having trouble with your conversion tracking. To help you better, could you please confirm if you are using Pixel or Postback for tracking? Once I have this information, I can provide more specific guidance.

Thanks for confirming that you're using Postback for tracking. Here are a few steps to ensure everything is set up correctly:
1. Make sure you have named your event and chosen 'Postback' as your event tracking type, 'ClickBank' as your 3rd party tracking service, and 'sale' as your conversion event in the dropdown.
2. Test the Postback integration by entering the URL you get from ClickBank (offer URL or test URL) and click 'Go test' to trigger your conversion event.
3. Ensure that you are using the parameter 'tid' in your URL to pass through the click ID: `tid=__CALLBACK_PARAM__`.
For detailed instructions, please refer to this article: [How to set up a ClickBank Postback on NewsBreak](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/23746617571341-How-to-set-up-a-ClickBank-Postback-on-NewsBreak).
If you've followed these steps and still face issues, please let me know!
